In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims Thursday, November 22, 2012, as a National Day of Thanksgiving. He highlights the importance of Thanksgiving as a time for Americans to gather with family and friends, reflect on their blessings, and show gratitude for the abundance in their lives. The President also emphasizes the spirit of compassion and mutual responsibility that has defined the nation since its early days. He mentions historical examples, such as the Pilgrims sharing a harvest with the Wampanoag tribe and President George Washington praying for peace and plenty. President Obama acknowledges the sacrifices of the men and women in uniform who cannot be with their families on Thanksgiving and expresses appreciation for those who serve their communities by providing meals and shelter to those in need. He encourages Americans to come together on this day of thanks, lift up their loved ones, and share their blessings with others.